title: For Sale:  1942 M1903-A3 transition rifle
postcontent: This is a 1942 Springfield M1903-A3. The information I gathered was that during the process of changing from the M1903 to the M1903-A3 they continued to use the machined parts until they were gone. This caused some of the new A3 models to have a mix of original M1903 machines parts and A3 stamped parts. This rifle appears to have it's original machines rear ladder sight but the fore sight and trigger guard are stamped. The stock is a very nice, hand checkered stock. Only the furniture appears to have been sporterized! This means a reversion to original is still possible, and even quite easy to do.
